article.headline: Oral Roberts 76, Wichita State 73
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- Freshman Ken Tutt hit three-of-four free throws in the final seconds of the game Tuesday to lead Oral Roberts past Wichita State 76-73. The score was tied at 73 when Wichita State (8-3) guard Fridge Holman fouled Tutt with two seconds left. Holman, frustrated with the call, took off his head band and threw it down the court, drawing a technical foul. Tutt sank two free throws on the technical foul to give Oral Roberts (7-4) a 75-73 lead, then hit the second of two free throws on the personal foul. He finished the game with 25 points. Oral Roberts took the lead at 50-49 with 11:28 left. The Shockers, who led at halftime 39-33, tied the score at 73 with 20 seconds left on a pair of Paul Miller free throws. Caleb Green, who fouled out on that play, finished with 22 points and 11 rebounds for the Golden Eagles. In addition to Tutt and Green, Josh Atkinson was in double figures for Oral Roberts with 11 points. Wichita State, which had a three-game winning streak snapped, was led by Jamar Howard's 21 points and 11 rebounds. He scored six of the Shockers' final eight points. Holman finished with 17 points for Wichita State.
